   <narrative xml:lang="EN">EMPOWER 60 FAMILIES WITH SUSTAINABLE AGRICULTURE</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Puente a la Salud Comunitaria aims to empower 60 small-scale farmers in Oaxaca, Mexico, providing training, tools, and agro-ecological farm inputs to allow them to grow amaranth and other crops in a sustainable and natural process. Amaranth is considered a superfood because of its nutritious properties, resistance to climate change and potential market value. Thus, they will produce healthy food that prevents degrading their soils and water sources and also reduce certain health risks.</narrative>
  </description>
